> Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Creamy Pesto Bacon and Asparagus Orzo in just 20-25 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @orzo{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @asparagus{100%g} and cut into thirds.

2 mins before the pasta has finished cooking, add the asparagus to the orzo and cook until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain the pasta and asparagus in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}. Stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Stir in the garlic and fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir the @creme fraiche{150%ml}, @vegetable stock paste{15%g}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{75%ml} into the pan. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, add the @baby spinach{100%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir through the @fresh pesto{32%g}, @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} and @butter{20%g} until the cheese and butter have melted.

Stir the cooked orzo and asparagus into the sauce until piping hot.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Share the creamy pesto orzo between your serving #bowls{}.

Drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}. Enjoy!